1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 34-05 and a new subsection to
2 section 34-05-01.3 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to the labor commissioner's
3 oversight of certain landlord-tenant disputes.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 34-05 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
6 and enacted as follows:
7 Failure to comply - Disciplinary action - Notice - How served .
8 1. The labor commissioner shall receive and investigate complaints from a tenant and
9 take disciplinary action against a landlord upon the failure of the landlord to comply
10 with sections 47 - 16 - 20 and 47 - 32 - 02, or any rules adopted by the labor commissioner
11 to enforce sections 47 - 16 - 20 and 47 - 32 - 02 .
12 2. Before the labor commissioner may take disciplinary action against a landlord for a
13 violation under this section, the labor commissioner shall notify the landlord in writing
14 of the reason disciplinary action is being considered and provide a reasonable time for
15 the landlord to correct the violation.
16 3. The notice required under subsection 2 must be delivered personally by the labor
17 commissioner or the commissioner's agent, or sent by registered or certified mail.
18 4. Any disciplinary action taken against a landlord under this section must comply with
19 chapter 28 - 32 .
20 SECTION 2. A new subsection to section 34-05-01.3 of the North Dakota Century Code is
21 created and enacted as follows:
22 Receive and investigate complaints from tenants and take disciplinary action against
23 landlords failing to comply with sections 47 - 16 - 20 and 47 - 32 - 02 .
